<h4 id="jekyll">Jekyll</h4>
<ol>
  <li>jekyll server</li>
  <li>jekyll serve –host=0.0.0.0
    <ul>
      <li>This will make Jekyll’s HTTP server bind to all available IPs.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="galois">Galois</h4>
<p>What’s the nature of a plugin?  It is used to extend functionality of
something.</p>
<ul>
  <li>Plugins of vim, extending vim’s functionality, are the corresponding command
you can execute at the bottom of vim in the command mode.</li>
  <li>Plugins of jekyll, extending jekyll’s ability, are the corresponding tags in
the template file, page file, etc.</li>
</ul>

